    <PrimAttribute name="drawX1" id="d305ff7f-e9fe-4ee9-b3ad-73c82d4d03ca">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Real"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>

This is the left poistion of the top left point of the graphic.

This will be the same by hold. This means that all the graphics for a bay within the hold are the same on each bay.

When drawing the second or third bay in a hold an offset will be needed.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="drawX2Width" id="4d5648e4-228a-4dfa-b6cd-0c98eb5dde40">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Real"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="drawY1" id="b0712c17-c63b-4c6a-aa4a-2a46022be0b6">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Real"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>

This is the top poistion of the top left point of the graphic.

This will be the same by hold. This means that all the graphics for a bay within the hold are the same on each bay.

When drawing the second or third bay in a hold an offset may be needed.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="drawY2Height" id="df42b0ea-c2d0-4292-814f-e5f1df922230">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Real"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="geometryPath" id="2e573b15-1115-43a7-9bfd-513a73d4bd1f">
        <type name="String"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>

EXAMPLE:

&lt;Path Data="M0.5,0.5 L280.5,44.5 M0.50000042,0.50000495 L111.523,110.81001 M280,45.000008 L112.5,109.50001" Margin="8,150,0,0"/&gt;



See String::convertXAMLPathToRealArray() for more detail</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
